The success confirmation screen is shown once payments have been successfully made to the recipient. The recipient information and payment information are
displayed on separate cards. Selecting ‘View Payment Details’ will take the user to the payment details screen, while selecting ‘View Recipient Details’ will take
the user to the Recipient Details page.
One Time Payment - New Recipient / Payment Confirmation
The creation of a payment will prompt this One Time Password Step Up Authentication step. This step ensures the safety of the company and personal
information. Users receive the security code to the phone number associated with their profile. This screen is consistent with what is used for Step Up
Authentication throughout the system (the contents in this design may differ from actual implementation).
The review payment screen displays the recipient information and all payment details they have entered in this flow.
If the user decides to save the recipient to the OU’s recipient list, a success alert banner appears at the top of the browser window to inform the
user that the recipient has been added. The user continues through the flow by entering payment information.
One Time Payment - Enter Payment - Recipient Added Success Banner
The user is then able to review new recipient details before continuing with payment details. At this step, the user is able to choose if they would
like to save the recipient that is receiving this one time payment or continue with payment without saving.
Next step in adding a new recipient is to enter account information. At least one account is required to make a payment.
One Time Payment - Enter Account Information
Creating a one time payment begins with creating a new recipient. The user starts by adding basic information. The required and optional fields
One Time Payment - Enter Recipient Information
The success confirmation screen is shown once payments have been successfully made to the recipient. In cases where multiple payments are made to the
same company, the cards are differentiated by the payment amount and recipient account. The user has the option on this page to return to the Payments
Landing page by selecting ‘Done’ CTA, or start the Payment Creation flow again by clicking on ‘Send another payment’ CTA. Selecting ‘View Payment Details’
text link will take the user to the respective Payment Details page.
The creation of a payment will prompt this One Time Password Step Up Authentication step. This step ensures the safety of the company and personal
information. Users receive the security code to the phone number associated with their profile. This screen is consistent with what is used for Step Up
Authentication throughout the system (the contents in this design may differ from actual implementation).
The review payment screen displays the recipient and all payment details. The user has the option to edit the information they already inputted
or select ‘Send Payment’ CTA to confirm the payment details.
This screen shows an instance in which multiple payments will be made to the same recipient. Selecting the ‘Add Another Payment’ text link will
cause another payment card to appear.
Payment Creation - Enter Payment (two or more payments)
On the Enter Payment page, payment details are entered. If the user wishes to see additional information on the recipient they have selected,
they can do so by selecting the ‘View Recipient Details’ text link. This will open a read-only overlay.
Payment entry fields may be pre-populated if the information is already known (for example, if there is only one account associated with the
recipient, it will be pre-selected). Remittance information is entered by selecting ‘Add’ text link next to ‘Additional information’.
This page is triggered by selecting the ‘Cadillac’ recipient name text link in the Payment Creation flow. On this page, there are no options for view
any other information other than what is provided on the screen, and the user is unable perform any actions on the recipient.
View Recipient Details (Read Only, second level overlay)
To create a payment to an existing recipient, the user would begin by searching for a recipient by the recipient name. The list of existing
recipients will be filtered to show recipients related to the search text. The user clicks a checkbox next to the recipient name and the selected
recipient will appear in a list to the right of the search and results area.
In the event where a user wants to have the payment sent to a non-existing recipient, the ‘Add a New Recipient’ text link and ‘One Time
Payment’ CTA are available and essentially lead to the same flow. The flow is surfaced to the user in several ways in order to minimize confusion
Payment Creation - Select Recipient - Search Results
This is the start of the ‘Create Payment’ flow, which can be accessed from the ‘View all’ CTA under ‘Make a payment to’ on the Payments
Landing page. On the default screen, the user can see a list of all their recipients. They can choose to select one or more recipient from the list,
search for an existing recipient, or make a one time payment to a new recipient.
